PKK Fighter’s Funeral in Turkey Draws 30,000, Milliyet Reports

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-05-23T06:43:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/pkk-fighter-s-funeral-in-turkey-draws-30-000-milliyet-reports.html
About 30,000 people joined a funeral
for a member of the Kurdistan Workers’ Party, or PKK, killed in
a firefight with Turkish security forces,  Milliyet  newspaper
reported.  Members of the pro-Kurdish Peace and Democracy Party, which
runs several municipalities and has seats in parliament, were
among those attending the funeral for Ramazan Terzioglu in
Yuksekova in southeastern  Turkey , Milliyet said.  Clashes between police and demonstrators were broken up
using tear gas and water cannons, Milliyet said.  The PKK is considered a terrorist organization by Turkey,
the U.S. and the European Union.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  